#. <section class="sutta" id="sn9.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga"
msgstr "1. In the Woods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn9.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Kassapagottasutta"
msgstr "3. With Kassapagotta"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.3:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā kassapagotto kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Kassapagotta was staying in the land of the Kosalans "
"in a certain forest grove."

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/what-does-cheta-mean/3593
msgctxt "sn9.3:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā kassapagotto divāvihāragato aññataraṃ chetaṃ "
"ovadati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Kassapagotta, having withdrawn for his day’s "
"meditation, tried to advise a tribal hunter."

msgctxt "sn9.3:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā āyasmantaṃ kassapagottaṃ "
"saṃvejetukāmā yenāyasmā kassapagotto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ "
"kassapagottaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the deity haunting that forest approached Kassapagotta wanting to stir "
"him up, and recited these verses:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.428"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.3:2.1"
msgid "“Giriduggacaraṃ chetaṃ,"
msgstr "“A tribal hunter wandering the rugged hills"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:2.2"
msgid "appapaññaṃ acetasaṃ;"
msgstr "is unintelligent, unthinking."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:2.3"
msgid "Akāle ovadaṃ bhikkhu,"
msgstr "It’s a waste of time to advise him;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:2.4"
msgid "mandova paṭibhāti maṃ."
msgstr "this mendicant seems to me like an idiot."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.3:3.1"
msgid "Suṇāti na vijānāti,"
msgstr "The tribal hunter listens without understanding,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:3.2"
msgid "Āloketi na passati;"
msgstr "he looks without seeing."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:3.3"
msgid "Dhammasmiṃ bhaññamānasmiṃ,"
msgstr "Though the teaching is spoken,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:3.4"
msgid "Atthaṃ bālo na bujjhati."
msgstr "the fool doesn’t get it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.199"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.3:4.1"
msgid "Sacepi dasa pajjote,"
msgstr "Even if you lit ten lamps"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:4.2"
msgid "dhārayissasi kassapa;"
msgstr "and brought them to him, Kassapa,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:4.3"
msgid "Neva dakkhati rūpāni,"
msgstr "he wouldn’t see anything,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.3:4.4"
msgid "cakkhu hissa na vijjatī”ti."
msgstr "for he has no eyes to see.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.3:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā kassapagotto tāya devatāya saṃvejito saṃvegamāpādīti."
msgstr "Stirred up by that deity, Venerable Kassapagotta came to his senses."
